<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
As an adverb @HI{{@EM{{amari}}}} is usually found in negative sentences. When it appears in a positive sentence it means "very" or "too" but with a negative implication.
</p>

<p>
@HI{{anmari}} is a variant of @HI{{@EM{{amari}}}} sometimes found in conversation.
</p>

<p>
As a conjunction @HI{{@EM{{amari}}}} is always part of a clause that expresses a cause.
It can only be used when the noun or verb expresses a psychological state.
Finally, the use of @HI{{@EM{{amari}}}} as a conjunction is limited to formal written Japanese.
</p>

